  "text": "## E0505 Error Trace: Move While Borrowed\n\n### Detection Flow:\n\n**1. MIR Borrow Checker Initialization (lib.rs)**\nThe MIR borrow checker is the core MirBorrowckCtxt struct (lib.rs:714) that implements the ResultsVisitor trait. It processes each MIR statement and terminator to detect borrow violations.\n\n**2. Move Operation Entry Point (lib.rs:1706-1750, consume_operand)**\nWhen the MIR analysis encounters an `Operand::Move(place)` operation (line 1732), the `consume_operand` function is triggered. This function checks if the move is legal by calling:\n- `check_movable_place()` - validates the source is movable (line 1734)\n- `access_place()` with `WriteKind::Move` - checks for borrow conflicts (line 1737-1743)\n\n**3. Conflict Detection (lib.rs:1179-1374, access_place and check_access_for_conflict)**\nThe `access_place` function (line 1179) is the central point for all access checking. It delegates to `check_access_for_conflict()` (line 1219) which:\n- Iterates through all borrows in scope using `borrows_in_scope()` (line 1256)\n- For each active borrow, checks if the move operation conflicts with it (line 1258-1371)\n- When `WriteKind::Move` is detected against an active borrow (line 1361), it calls `report_move_out_while_borrowed()`\n\n**4. Error Reporting (conflict_errors.rs:1533-1599, report_move_out_while_borrowed)**\nThis function (line 1533) is the critical error reporting function that:\n- Retrieves borrow span information (line 1546-1547)\n- Gets move span information (line 1549-1550)\n- Calls `cannot_move_when_borrowed()` to create the error (line 1552-1558)\n- Adds diagnostic context and suggestions (line 1559-1597)\n\n**5. Diagnostic Creation (borrowck_errors.rs:16-31, cannot_move_when_borrowed)**\nThis function creates the error diagnostic by instantiating the `MoveBorrow` struct with:\n- span: location of the move operation\n- borrow_span: location of the conflicting borrow\n- place, borrow_place, value_place: descriptive names for error message\n\n**6. Error Message Struct (session_diagnostics.rs:284-295, MoveBorrow)**\nThe `MoveBorrow` struct is decorated with:\n```\n#[derive(Diagnostic)]\n#[diag(borrowck_cannot_move_when_borrowed, code = E0505)]\npub(crate) struct MoveBorrow<'a>\n```\nThis struct generates the error message \"cannot move out of {place} because it is borrowed\" (from messages.ftl:25-26)\n\n**7. Error Code Documentation (E0505.md)**\nThe error code documentation file explains:\n- What the error means (value moved while borrowed)\n- Why it occurred (move happens before borrow ends)\n- How to fix it (release borrow before move, pass by reference, implement Copy, or reorder code)\n\n### Key Files and Functions:\n\n1. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs** (main borrow checker logic)\n   - `MirBorrowckCtxt` struct (line 714): The context containing all borrow checking state\n   - `consume_operand` function (line 1706): Entry point for move operations\n   - `access_place` function (line 1179): Dispatcher for access conflict checking\n   - `check_access_for_conflict` function (line 1246): Core conflict detection logic (line 1361-1362 for move-while-borrowed)\n\n2. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/diagnostics/conflict_errors.rs**\n   - `report_move_out_while_borrowed` function (line 1533): Reports E0505 error\n\n3. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrowck_errors.rs**\n   - `cannot_move_when_borrowed` function (line 16): Creates the error diagnostic\n\n4. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/session_diagnostics.rs**\n   - `MoveBorrow` struct (line 285): Diagnostic definition with code = E0505\n\n5. **compiler/rustc_error_codes/src/error_codes/E0505.md**\n   - Error explanation and fixes\n\nThe error is triggered when: (1) A move operation is detected (Operand::Move), (2) An active borrow exists over the same location, (3) The borrow would be invalidated by the move (checked via borrow kind and location analysis), resulting in error E0505."
