or message\n\n**6. Error Message Struct (session_diagnostics.rs:284-295, MoveBorrow)**\nThe `MoveBorrow` struct is decorated with:\n```\n#[derive(Diagnostic)]\n#[diag(borrowck_cannot_move_when_borrowed, code = E0505)]\npub(crate) struct MoveBorrow<'a>\n```\nThis struct generates the error message \"cannot move out of {place} because it is borrowed\" (from messages.ftl:25-26)\n\n**7. Error Code Documentation (E0505.md)**\nThe error code documentation file explains:\n- What the error means (value moved while borrowed)\n- Why it occurred (move happens before borrow ends)\n- How to fix it (release borrow before move, pass by reference, implement Copy, or reorder code)\n\n### Key Files and Functions:\n\n1. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs** (main borrow checker logic)\n   - `MirBorrowckCtxt` struct (line 714): The context containing all borrow checking state\n   - `consume_operand` function (line 1706): Entry point for move operations\n   - `access_place` function (line 1179): Dispatcher for access conflict checking\n   - `check_access_for_conflict` function (line 1246): Core conflict detection logic (line 1361-1362 for move-while-borrowed)\n\n2. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/diagnostics/conflict_errors.rs**\n   - `report_move_out_while_borrowed` function (line 1533): Reports E0505 error\n\n3. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrowck_errors.rs**\n   - `cannot_move_when_borrowed` function (line 16): Creates the error diagnostic\n\n4. **compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/session_diagnostics.rs**\n   - `MoveBorrow` struct (line 285): Diagnostic definition with code = E0505\n\n5. **compiler/rustc_error_codes/src/error_codes/E0505.md**\n   - Error explanation and fixes\n\nThe error is triggered when: (1) A move operation is detected (Operand::Move), (2) An active borrow exists over the same location, (3) The borrow would be invalidated by the move (checked via borrow kind and location analysis), resulting in error E0505."
